<div type="definition">
<p>WATER FALLING FROM CLOUDS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for rain of any kind is yǔ 雨.</p>
<p>2. Lín 霖 refers to a lengthy period of rain or abundant rains of any kind..</p>
<p>3. Fēng yǔ 風雨 refers to a rainstorm.</p>
<p>4. Léi yǔ 雷雨 refers to a thunderstorm.</p>
        </div>
